</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,1600,2030]" pageId="6" pageNumber="367">
Yellow, head with 
<number box="[410,424,1637,1661]" pageId="6" pageNumber="367" value="2.0">2</number>
pairs of black rounded spots, one on the anterior margin and another on posterior margin of vertex. Forewings with smoky brown bands on the clavus and corium.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,1600,2030]" pageId="6" pageNumber="367">
Male abdomen. 
<number box="[379,393,1711,1735]" pageId="6" pageNumber="367" value="2.0">2</number>
nd acrotergite with trunk widely V-shaped, lateral processes elongate, neck short, less than half of trunk width. 
<number box="[336,350,1751,1775]" pageId="6" pageNumber="367" value="2.0">2</number>
nd tergal apodeme reaching 
<number box="[668,678,1751,1775]" pageId="6" pageNumber="367" value="1.0">1</number>
/ 
<number box="[689,704,1751,1775]" pageId="6" pageNumber="367" value="2.0">2</number>
of tergite posteriorly, median projection reaching the posterior margin. 
<number box="[244,258,1789,1813]" pageId="6" pageNumber="367" value="1.0">1</number>
st sternal apodeme with posterior lobes round, longer than wide. 
<number box="[974,988,1789,1813]" pageId="6" pageNumber="367" value="2.0">2</number>
nd sternal apodeme well-developed, with posterior lobes about 
<number box="[393,428,1824,1849]" pageId="6" pageNumber="367" value="2.5">2.5</number>
times as long as basal width, distinctly extending beyond sternum margin.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,1600,2030]" pageId="6" pageNumber="367">Male genitalia. Pygofer broad, with a distinct caudo-ventral tubercle, spinulose; aedeagal shaft slightly broad, smooth and straight; apical appendages crossed medially and bent caudally.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
