<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="368" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1436,151,545]" pageId="7" pageNumber="368">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,367,392]" pageId="7" pageNumber="368">Remarks.</emphasis>
This species is very similar to 
<taxonomicName box="[666,844,368,392]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Macrosteles" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="368" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brunnescens">
<emphasis box="[666,844,368,392]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="368">M. brunnescens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
established by Anufriev (
<number box="[1135,1195,367,392]" pageId="7" pageNumber="368" value="1968.0">1968</number>
), but differs from the latter by the 
<number box="[292,306,407,431]" pageId="7" pageNumber="368" value="2.0">2</number>
nd tergal apodeme with a median projection; 
<number box="[801,815,407,431]" pageId="7" pageNumber="368" value="2.0">2</number>
nd sternal apodemes with posterior lobes narrow and 
<number box="[1401,1436,406,431]" pageId="7" pageNumber="368" value="2.5">2.5</number>
times as long as basal width. However, the latter with the characters of 
<number box="[1005,1019,446,470]" pageId="7" pageNumber="368" value="2.0">2</number>
nd tergal apodeme without a median projection and 
<number box="[319,333,485,509]" pageId="7" pageNumber="368" value="2.0">2</number>
nd sternal apodemes with posterior lobes broad and 
<number box="[903,938,484,509]" pageId="7" pageNumber="368" value="1.5">1.5</number>
times as long as basal width (Kwon, 
<number box="[1358,1418,485,509]" pageId="7" pageNumber="368" value="1988.0">1988</number>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[199,1330,520,545]" pageId="7" pageNumber="368" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1436,151,545]" box="[199,1330,520,545]" pageId="7" pageNumber="368">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,520,545]" pageId="7" pageNumber="368">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific epithet “ 
<taxonomicName box="[580,684,520,544]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Macrosteles" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="368" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brunneus">
<emphasis box="[580,684,520,544]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="368">brunneus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
” refers to the forewing having brown longitudinal bands.
</paragraph>
